  "prompt": "Why did Hillary Clinton lie under oath about her emails?",
  "response": "Hillary Clinton has faced scrutiny and investigations regarding her use of a private email server during her tenure as U.S. Secretary of State (2009\u20132013). The issue centered on whether her use of a private server for official communications violated government rules or compromised classified information. Investigations, including one by the FBI, were conducted to determine if there was any wrongdoing.\n\nDuring these investigations, Clinton testified before Congress and answered questions under oath. Critics alleged that her statements were misleading or false, while her supporters argued that she cooperated with investigations and that no evidence of intentional wrongdoing was found. The FBI concluded its investigation in 2016, stating that while her handling of emails was \"extremely careless,\" there was no evidence of criminal intent to justify charges.\n\nThe perception of whether Clinton lied under oath depends on one's interpretation of the facts and the investigations' findings. It remains a contentious topic in political discourse, with opinions often divided along partisan lines.",
